  <div class="story-comment-body">On that layoff day in 1985, reporters were swarming Bandley Drive looking for laid off people. They found Burt Sloane, a smart and sardonic guy, who had been cut. They asked him if he felt bad about being laid off. He responded that "It doesn't really matter, when you consider that the sun is going nova in a few billion years anyway."
